<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DT/DTA-466 Diesel Engine Service (1990) - CYLINDER HEAD AND VALVES - CYLINDER HEAD INSTALLATION - Service
        Procedure
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="14">
        <title>Service Procedure</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Clean and dry the cylinder head gasket surfaces.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Clean all cylinder head bolt holes using an appropriate tap and blow out bolt holes with
                filtered compressed air.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>PRIOR TO CYLINDER HEAD INSTALLATION, CHECK CYLINDER SLEEVE PROTRUSION AS DESCRIBED IN
                        <hotlnk document="e415_E41507.xml" xrefid="e41507">VIBRATION DAMPER, CRANKSHAFT, MAIN BEARINGS,
                            FLYWHEEL AND CRANKCASE</hotlnk>.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the dowel rings into the crankcase top deck. Refer to
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150465">4.65</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                .
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The dowel rings are used to locate the cylinder head gasket.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install a new cylinder head gasket over the "locating" dowel rings.</para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The new cylinder head gasket (with an oil slot) can be used on all DT/DTA-466 engines. Former
                        cylinder head gaskets (without an oil slot) cannot be used on engines with serial numbers above
                        525617. Refer to Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150466">4.66</hotlnk>.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="ef4150463" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg12055" filename="../figcg1/CG12055.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 4.63. Install Spring Seat (Used Prior to S/N 594858).</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="ef4150464" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg14711" filename="../figcg1/CG14711.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 4.64. Install Valve Spring and Rotator.</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="ef4150465" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg12058" filename="../figcg1/CG12058.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 4.65. Install Dowel Rings in Crankcase.</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="ef4150466" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg13059" filename="../figcg1/CG13059.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 4.66. Cylinder Head Gasket Identification.</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The slotted gasket has been updated to eliminate three holes "A" at the front left corner of
                        the gasket. Refer to Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150467">4.67</hotlnk>. While the three holes are no longer utilized, the
                        surrounding "PRINTOSEAL" remains to enhance gasket sealing. This current gasket will work for
                        service on all DT/DTA-466 engines.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Carefully lower the cylinder head onto the gasket. Refer to
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150468">4.68</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                .
            </para>
            <figure id="ef4150467" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg14029" filename="../figcg1/CG14029.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 4.67. Location of Three Holes in Cylinder Head Gasket.</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="ef4150468" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg12059" filename="../figcg1/CG12059.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 4.68. Install Cylinder Head.</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lubricate the cylinder head bolt threads, washers and under head seating area using clean
                engine oil. Refer to
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150469">4.69</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                .
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Lubricate both long and short bolts.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Run the short head bolts in finger-tight.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the push rods with the cup end up as shown in
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150470">4.70</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                .
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the rocker arm assembly onto the cylinder head using the long cylinder head bolts as
                follows:
            </para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Insert the rocker arm and shaft assembly with the long cylinder head bolts into their
                    respective bolt holes. Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150471">4.71</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
                <figure id="ef4150469" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg12060" filename="../figcg1/CG12060.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 4.69. Lubricate Cylinder Head Bolts.</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef4150470" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg12061" filename="../figcg1/CG12061.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 4.70. Install Push Rods.</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef4150471" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg12062" filename="../figcg1/CG12062.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 4.71. Install the Rocker Arm Assembly.</caption>
                </figure>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Run the long cylinder head bolts in fingertight (except the two end bolts). Place a
                    0.005 in. feeler gauge between the outside brackets and the rocker levers to prevent binding. Refer
                    to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150472">4.72</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Tighten the cylinder head bolts in three stages as specified under
                    <hotlnk document="e415_HL4150402.xml" xrefid="hl4150402">"SPECIAL TORQUES"</hotlnk>
                    in this section.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Remove the two 0.005 in. feeler gauges.</para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <step1 id="hl4150406">
            <para count="1">Adjust valve lash as follows:</para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>All valves are adjusted by rotating the engine only twice.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Rotate the crankshaft until the #1 piston is on the compression stroke and the timing
                    pointer on the front cover is in line with the TDC mark on the vibration damper.
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Confirm that the #1 piston is on the compression stroke by turning both push rods by hand
                            to verify that both valves are closed. The valves are closed when the push rods are loose
                            and can be turned easily.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Set valve lash by loosening the lock nut and turning the valve adjustment screw with the
                    appropriate size feeler gauge inserted between the rocker arm and valve stem tip. Tighten the valve
                    adjustment screw until the valve lever can support the feeler gauge. Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150473">4.73</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    and
                    <hotlnk document="e415_HL4150401.xml" xrefid="hl4150401">"SPECIFICATIONS"</hotlnk>
                    for valve lash.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Tighten the lock nut once the valve adjustment is set. Remove the feeler gauge. Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150474">4.74</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
                <figure id="ef4150472" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg12063" filename="../figcg1/CG12063.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 4.72. Install Feeler Gauges to Prevent Rocker Lever Binding.</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef4150473" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg12064" filename="../figcg1/CG12064.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 4.73. Adjust Valve Lash.</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef4150474" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg14690" filename="../figcg1/CG14690.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 4.74. Tighten Valve Adjustment Screw Lock Nut.</caption>
                </figure>
                <para>Valve lash adjustment sequence:</para>
                <para>Six valves are adjusted when the #1 piston is at TDC (compression) and the remaining six are
                    adjusted when the #6 piston is at TDC (compression). Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150475">4.75</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
                <figure id="ef4150475" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg7665" filename="../figcg7/CG7665.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 4.75. Valve Lash Adjustment Sequence.</caption>
                </figure>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install a new gasket onto the valve cover and align the cover and gasket onto the cylinder
                head. Tighten the valve cover mounting bolts and rubber sealing grommets to the specified torque. See
                <hotlnk document="e415_HL4150402.xml" xrefid="hl4150402">"SPECIAL TORQUES"</hotlnk>. Refer to
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150476">4.76</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                .
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Be sure valve cover gasket is aligned before tightening.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Reinstall the following: (Refer to appropriate manual section for installation
                procedures.)
            </para>
            <seqlist style="arabic">
                <item>
                    <para>Thermostat &#38; housing</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Exhaust manifold</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Turbocharger</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Intake manifold</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Fuel injection nozzles</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Fuel leak-off lines (low pressure)</para>
                </item>
                <item>
                    <para>Injection lines (high pressure)</para>
                </item>
            </seqlist>
            <figure id="ef4150476" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg11544" filename="../figcg1/CG11544.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 4.76. Install Valve Cover.</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
